"""
Note that the struture of the svg's generated by anki are as follows:
svg tag, defs tag, path tags, use tags. The path tags are used to
define the symbols used inside the svg. Note also that the same symbol
in the same context is generated by exactly the same path tag on every
card, i.e. display math left brace. So, it might be viable to manually
create a mapping dictionary, mapping a symbol and context onto the
string representation of a path tag and determine the mapping between
svg's and anki notes by checking if each path object of the symbols
contained in the note where there is a mapping to a path object, is
contained in the string representation of the svg. The mapping might
not have to cover a big number of symbols, just enough to uniquely
identify the right svg. To take advantage of sequences of symbols, I
would need to be able to determine the id of each path tag, which
seems to differ between notes.
"""

